<subSubSection id="065EAF6B1D15F7A781BEA80994EAEA4F" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="43A0C96B8C7C2FF14FE24B1410D496CF" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7FE42053476AAE8973C8C72A5E9889BC" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">The species name was chosen after the Sagami Bay, from where the species was collected. It is an adjective agreeing with female gender of the genus.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="7B14B96E483EFECE1FAE2C1575B4C102" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="0564983FDFF5CD7E6C7B316A4E7CCCA8" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="85999DC002A862BF3A9D85E3E9972217" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">Surface of the shell completely smooth. Posterior infold of the carapace with a broad shelf. Dorsal margin rounded in female and almost perpendicular in male. Lateral eye well developed with black pigmented ommatidia, smaller in female than in male. A1 8-segmented without d-bristle on the 8th joint. Uropodal lamellae with eight claws.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="516379CBFA57410834C42646F7C22CB1" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" type="description">
<paragraph id="FBF56ACBF31A139FDAE2DF91741F070A" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4570310B64040286260B1D72D772273C" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis id="63D22C3EB0509514081A8B3927115034" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">Female.</emphasis>
Shell (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="F47F131B7CA5878EC442DAC20664C8F1" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Light microscopy and scanning electron microscopy images of Parasterope sagami sp. nov. a-c holotype female adult: a External view b Lateral view from right valve c Internal view from left valve. d-f paratype male adult: d External view e Lateral view from right valve f Internal view of left valve." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.77996.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/672093" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">5a-c</figureCitation>
). Carapace oval, broadening at posterior, greatest height near middle, carapace length 1.21 mm, height 0.83 mm. Carapace smooth and without ornamentation.
</paragraph>
<caption id="3C6B880D2C41F5B935519DB0A14450ED" doi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.77996.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/672093" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" start="Figure 5" startId="F5">
