</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="C2F417825E248218AF08914F5B83E113" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">
A2 (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="318A4AC6492A67A3C6591E44A45339A3" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Parasterope sagami sp. nov. holotype female adult: a A 1 b A 2 c Md. Scale bar: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.77996.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/672094" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">6b</figureCitation>
). Protopodite: rounded without medial bristle. Endopodite: 3-jointed with long terminal bristle near junction between 2nd and 3rd join. Exopodite: 9-jointed; bristle of 2nd segment along ventral margin and spines along dorsal margin reaching 8th joint; 3rd-8th joints with natatory hairs and spines along proximal part of ventral margin. 9th article: four bristles (two long natatory and two short bristles). 1st-8th with minute spines at inner terminal corner.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4D080D6A79F9245900B84EAD7239DCC4" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">
Md (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="D3328E673B5A7ABE71A9781F3E44F23A" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Parasterope sagami sp. nov. holotype female adult: a A 1 b A 2 c Md. Scale bar: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.77996.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/672094" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">6c</figureCitation>
). Coxale endite: unable to determine. Basale endite with four spinous end bristles, three triaenid bristles with three pairs spines excluding terminal pair. Basale dorsal margin with three long terminal setae, without mid-bristle. Exopodite with hirsute tip and two small subterminal setae, exopodite length ~ 
<normalizedToken id="79705E00067CDFC184DD7CB4889E720A" originalValue="¾">3/4</normalizedToken>
of dorsal margin of first endopodite article. Endopodite: 1st joint: ventral margin with three bristles (one missing, one long with long marginal spines, and one shorter without spine or hair); 2nd joint: ventral margin: with three terminal bristles; dorsal margin: with stout a-, b-, c-, and d-bristles and one short bristle proximal to a-bristle; e-bristle missing, two medial bristles adjacent to b-bristle; three medial bristles forming an oblique row adjacent to c-bristle; f-bristle between c- and d-bristle, long, bare; g-bristle shorter than f-bristle. End segment with a strong dorsal claw-like bristle without marginal spines, three juxtaposed stout bristles of equal length.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BAB6907156F319B8415A1A969DAAF327" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">
Mxl (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="2E534625FA38FE579A7C18A15D35E0EF" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Parasterope sagami sp. nov. holotype male adult: a Bellonci organ e Mxl f L 5 g L 6 h L 7 i F. Paratype male adult: b A 1 c A 2 endopodite d Md. Scale bar: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.77996.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/672095" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">7e</figureCitation>
). Endite I with three bristles. Endite II with four bristles. Basale: one dorsal medial distal bristle, two ventral medial proximal bristles. Endopodite: 1st with one short 
<normalizedToken id="516541DF839A22390BF221EB7FAA7025" originalValue="α-seta">α-seta</normalizedToken>
and one hairy 
<normalizedToken id="843C553EC3BA31DFDB1839C51AD1E101" originalValue="β-seta">β-seta</normalizedToken>
; 2nd article with two terminal bristles.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="70016AF2B46062ED376C3335632BCF3A" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">
L5 (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="8F620FE59F7E18F7AC1D57E739038F71" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Parasterope sagami sp. nov. holotype male adult: a Bellonci organ e Mxl f L 5 g L 6 h L 7 i F. Paratype male adult: b A 1 c A 2 endopodite d Md. Scale bar: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.77996.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/672095" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">7f</figureCitation>
). Ventral section with fan of long setae. Comb: spinous exopodite bristle over past distal end of comb, one bristle just proximal at the ventral edge of comb.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="44E99CAD36FB76E6145AAD7D52330B31" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">
L6 (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="318D766E961975D760481018A1F34289" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Parasterope sagami sp. nov. holotype male adult: a Bellonci organ e Mxl f L 5 g L 6 h L 7 i F. Paratype male adult: b A 1 c A 2 endopodite d Md. Scale bar: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.77996.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/672095" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">7g</figureCitation>
). Anterior margin with one endite bristle. Ventral margin with two spinous anterior bristles separated by space from 13 bristles. Anterior, ventral, and posterior margins, and medial surfaces hirsute. Lateral flap spinous but without bristles.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3902973BD94436B71345DB71D5C6F20A" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">
L7 (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="AAB922602543E96BEB8876D997099BEA" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Parasterope sagami sp. nov. holotype male adult: a Bellonci organ e Mxl f L 5 g L 6 h L 7 i F. Paratype male adult: b A 1 c A 2 endopodite d Md. Scale bar: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.77996.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/672095" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">7h</figureCitation>
). Each limb with 12 bristles. Six proximal and six distal bristles (three on each side).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="742BAAC267A1FBFC932A140489F70ED6" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">
F (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="A53271FC3BE18ADB2D6D76CF5CDC8C2D" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Parasterope sagami sp. nov. holotype male adult: a Bellonci organ e Mxl f L 5 g L 6 h L 7 i F. Paratype male adult: b A 1 c A 2 endopodite d Md. Scale bar: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.77996.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/672095" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">7i</figureCitation>
). Each lamella with five claws and three posterior claws bristle-like. A total of eight claws and bristles.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="256C6010814046B54D7269821E5A5EB4" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis id="97F6D4C2152E6779A5AFB63E3DFC0A0F" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">Male.</emphasis>
All features comparable to adult female; important differences are:
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="10F3BCFED6BDCF8989DF1B9C0E8A3A82" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">
Shell (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="6EAA87DF8FA035242F2EB7B35DCB43D4" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Light microscopy and scanning electron microscopy images of Parasterope sagami sp. nov. a-c holotype female adult: a External view b Lateral view from right valve c Internal view from left valve. d-f paratype male adult: d External view e Lateral view from right valve f Internal view of left valve." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.77996.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/672093" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">5d-f</figureCitation>
). Carapace more elongate than that of female and, carapace length 1.65 mm, height at middle 1.02 mm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DE3BB02C9F8D038F70E5D1F9B9A94D41" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">
A1 (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="522C90744F13A89EC1DBC1C646E93FEB" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Parasterope sagami sp. nov. holotype male adult: a Bellonci organ e Mxl f L 5 g L 6 h L 7 i F. Paratype male adult: b A 1 c A 2 endopodite d Md. Scale bar: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.77996.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/672095" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">7b</figureCitation>
). Sensory seta with robust stem and many filaments. 7th and 8th joints with very long c- and f-setae (long as carapace length) each with numerous of marginal filaments. 2nd joint with lateral bristle. 2nd and 4th joints without dorsal margin spines.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="775121107F2E2E79DD62EC64A1E92C2D" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis id="02D110B1033C54E0BC837AF31E1921BD" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis id="0A4461575315D8414EB8758EDD18658B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">Eyes</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Lateral eye with 18 ommatidia obscured by black pigment.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="753F54BC6B5D3858777B667EA2B487B6" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">
A2 (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="7DB2FC9EA26A1B41DC52855EFF2F1B26" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Parasterope sagami sp. nov. holotype male adult: a Bellonci organ e Mxl f L 5 g L 6 h L 7 i F. Paratype male adult: b A 1 c A 2 endopodite d Md. Scale bar: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.77996.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/672095" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">7c</figureCitation>
). Endopodite with three articles, article two with two lateral setae, article three recurved with one small proximal seta.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A2F53476F03F5D1D2139AF796593B77D" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">
Md (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="697C237BA881F7C34B881FDC07E47D88" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Parasterope sagami sp. nov. holotype male adult: a Bellonci organ e Mxl f L 5 g L 6 h L 7 i F. Paratype male adult: b A 1 c A 2 endopodite d Md. Scale bar: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.77996.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/672095" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">7d</figureCitation>
). Basale dorsal margin with two long terminal setae. Endopodite: 2nd joint: dorsal margin: with stout a-, b-bristles, c-and d-claws bristle-like, and two short bristles proximal to a-bristle; e-bristle present on male. Two oblique rows between b- and c-bristles (a row adjacent to b-bristle with four bristles, a row adjacent to c-claw bristle-like with six bristles).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BF6BA70FED6A311925C4EECDDF8B8D61" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis id="E4A02EDF3315EA07A8E7DDAB1C45BCDD" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis id="42DFA56E02AB7B29A217D96750666401" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">Reproductive organs</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="B934F8C4CD4F47B505DFEB1A15504495" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="7BC1B87106D4122BA457036C8F5B691B" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CF850738F08C29CE3BD32AC62C9556AF" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">
<taxonomicName id="E15EC6B533E4E808D58F88D54FD85BC1" authorityName="Pham &amp; Karanovic" authorityYear="2022" class="Ostracoda" family="Cylindroleberididae" genus="Parasterope" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Parasterope sagami" order="Myodocopida" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="sagami">
<emphasis id="97CBCFF974CABB0439FF258C3617149E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">Parasterope sagami</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from all other 
<taxonomicName id="EAD17C462899D7A7A41A6FAC05675B14" class="Ostracoda" family="Cylindroleberididae" genus="Parasterope" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Parasterope" order="Myodocopida" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D072FF669C01A8C5900FC1E4F1705319" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">Parasterope</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
representatives by the combination of the following characters:
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C0C833396B7360B70822596F7F3AFD6B" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis id="760BF7D646A2EF05A6C3FB0C097820B1" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">Female.</emphasis>
Dorsal margin of the Md basale has three long terminal setae next to the exopodite, and it has no mid-bristle. In addition, the A1 g-bristle has a peculiar shape, and there is no lateral bristle on the A1 2nd joint;
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3E874CF957D436259E0E6E071C8143DA" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis id="C5C03AD4E6D2411C5582A9C23F2B93AD" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">Male.</emphasis>
The presence of the c- and d-claws bristle-like on the Md endopodite 2nd joint in the adult males is unique for the new species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B92D67F04D71E4A5DB3E5BBC02297ABF" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">
In addition to the above characters, 
<taxonomicName id="ADE280FAC513A2613D6D21D12A7EDFEE" genus="P." lsidName="P. sagami" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" rank="species" species="sagami">
<emphasis id="F64885136AC0724CC4199EC03B5D1E28" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">P. sagami</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="C3ED5A36B30636352D0AD5378AB68E04" genus="P." lsidName="P. busanensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" rank="species" species="busanensis">
<emphasis id="565E7E67A5FC697712B02354E56C80CE" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">P. busanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the morphology of the endite II of Mxl. Namely, the endite carries three rather than four bristles. Also, the short 
<normalizedToken id="12714E9C5875F81460374F6115AAAF4C" originalValue="α-seta">α-seta</normalizedToken>
on the Mxl exopodite is absent in 
<taxonomicName id="DF9C8E73FC989F1E84EF405AF6B5FAF2" genus="P." lsidName="P. busanensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" rank="species" species="busanensis">
<emphasis id="8F03BF7A0E5CF3247BEE142ED301548D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">P. busanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1171962CD41AA81C3B1E433FE97B8AED" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">
<taxonomicName id="7BF69BEE588259A6A9DEB86FE0798322" authorityName="Poulsen" authorityYear="1965" class="Ostracoda" family="Cylindroleberididae" genus="Parasterope" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Parasterope jenseni" order="Myodocopida" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="jenseni">
<emphasis id="9711D66D5F08D3E6DFBBB0111F6D47FA" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">Parasterope jenseni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was also described from Sagami Sea, Japan (
<bibRefCitation id="E3DF11F134F9E74FC909119DC7671E16" author="Poulsen, EM" journalOrPublisher="Marine Biodiversity" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" refId="B33" refString="Poulsen, EM, 1965. Ostracoda - Myodocopa, Part II: Cypridiniformes - Rutidermatidae, Sarsiellidae and Asteropidae. Dana Report Carlsberg Foundation (65): 1-484." title="Ostracoda - Myodocopa, Part II: Cypridiniformes - Rutidermatidae, Sarsiellidae and Asteropidae. Dana Report Carlsberg Foundation (65): 1 - 484." year="1965">Poulsen 1965</bibRefCitation>
) and it also has no lateral bristle on the A1 2nd joint. It differs from 
<taxonomicName id="B001A57287F4B3754332B8F14F93BEBB" genus="P." lsidName="P. sagami" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" rank="species" species="sagami">
<emphasis id="80B312D5346F2156B7909AB5944C0280" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">P. sagami</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having small lateral eyes with ~ 10 ommatidia; a long stem of the sensory bristle (~ 4 
<normalizedToken id="F4FBBAE6294B45388822722ACC28A631" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
the length of the 6th joint); and the presence of spines on the ventral margin of the protopodite of A2 (
<bibRefCitation id="09E337D9CA4DD808C426387F5AED26FE" author="Poulsen, EM" journalOrPublisher="Marine Biodiversity" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" refId="B33" refString="Poulsen, EM, 1965. Ostracoda - Myodocopa, Part II: Cypridiniformes - Rutidermatidae, Sarsiellidae and Asteropidae. Dana Report Carlsberg Foundation (65): 1-484." title="Ostracoda - Myodocopa, Part II: Cypridiniformes - Rutidermatidae, Sarsiellidae and Asteropidae. Dana Report Carlsberg Foundation (65): 1 - 484." year="1965">Poulsen 1965</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="70ACFC631802E2F5051484AA97B9260E" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">
<taxonomicName id="9D7D91A732403BD82FB70AB61B699EB7" authorityName="Poulsen" authorityYear="1965" class="Ostracoda" family="Cylindroleberididae" genus="Parasterope" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Parasterope obesa" order="Myodocopida" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="obesa">
<emphasis id="34B026BBE32899D2E794365E69D80995" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">Parasterope obesa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Poulsen, 1965 from Misaki, Japan has a lateral bristle on the 2nd joint of A1 which is absent in the two above species; 4th joint of the A1 is without lateral spines on the ventral margin otherwise present in the new species; and there are more than ten bristles on the ventral edge of the comb.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DC30E7A8E483DBA24B25F054FEBA10EC" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">GenBank numbers 16S: OK048683, OK048684; 18S: OK048721, OK048722.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
